history.text: Hi!  How are you doing tonight?
great u?
Pretty good...wish there was something good on t.v.
toy story is a great movie. It was my favorite as a child.
That'd be great if it was on!  How many Toy Story movies are there, anyway?
I believe there are 5 movies now
I think I've only seen 3 of them, then. I liked them all!
Yes.. did you know tom hanks was the voice of woody and tim allen was buzz?
I did know that!  There were some other famous "voices" in them too, I think.
yes. don rickles was mr potato head, jim varney was the slinky dog, and wallace shawn was rex. At least those were the famous actors in the 1st movie
Wallace Shawn...that name I don't know.  What else has he done?
I do not know, but the movie was also executive-produced by steve jobs.
That's part of the fun of watching TS...figuring out the different voices!

Yes. It is a very imaginative movie. That is appealing
 to both kids and adults.
I don't think there's a Pixar movie I don't like.
Me too. My favorite character is mr. Potato head.
Mine is Jessie from TS2.
...and the little shorts they do before the movie are as good as the movie!
Yep I agree! my favorite scene in toy story is when they go to the space arcade and get stuck in the crane game.
The little green army men are pretty hilarious, too.
There's so much of the movie I like, but I've forgotten alot of the little details.  Makes me want to go watch it again.
Is there any good music in the TS movies?
Hello?  Still there??
